<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9693000187707></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9693000187707><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=search.shtml?faction=38&mid=9693000187707>Get faction up with use of an Enchanter</a> <a id=fs8 href=search.shtml?faction=38&mid=9693000187707#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 2:00 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi all,<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   First I just wanted to say that I was extremely KOS to bards at one time.  I'm an enchanter and even with the use of Benevolence they were still "scowling".  I spent about 2 days in Mistmoore with no success.  I had heard, however, that factions are best raised through questing, instead of killing.  I found out that this is so.  Unfortunately, all bard quests involved associations with bards.  I thought for a while and came up with an idea, and it worked.  I looked at the name of the faction and noticed it said "Antonican" bards.  So I went to the bard house in Kelethin, under invisibility and conned them all one at a time.  I would target one, run out, cancel my invis, and hit "C" for con.  Only 2 were of the Antonican bard faction, both of them green.<br><br>First of all, I proceeded to Felwithe, and saw Ticar Tissleplay right inside of the zone.  I charmed him and was happy to find that he allowed me to receive the letter from him, as well as my friend who was also KOS to Antonican Bards.  I then proceeded back to Kelethin to give our letters to Jakum Webdancer.  However, there was another "green" bard in there.  After thinking, my warrior friend proceeded into the bard hall and both of them jumped him.  He ran out and I mesmerized the other one, besides Jakum Webdancer.  None of the other bards came, much to our satisfaction.  He was levitated by me just in case he had to zone, and was SoWed as well.  But no other bards came, since they weren't "Antonican" bards, being that they resided on the continent of Faydwer.  After Jakum's friend was mesmerized, I charmed him and was glad to see that he accepted our letters and we got faction.  After doing this about 20 times, plus or minus (not sure), my warrior friend ran inside to pull the 2 bards, but they wouldn't aggro on him.  He conned them and they were dubious, so I used /assist on him so my target would jump to Jakum and hit "C" for con, and he was dubious.  This took no more than 30 times to do, and only having to zone once.  I was able to gate to Felwithe, my friend had to run however.  <br><br>Anyway, this was how I got my faction back.  Hope this helps.  Good luck!<br><br>Sikira Boh<br>Level 40 Enchantress<br>Guild---Aqua Vitae<br>Povar Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
